RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 1 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 73. Claiming Purse 23000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500 (Maidens Races Not Considered In Eligibility).

CLAIM.OWNER: Han Moon S and Han Soon H

RACE.FOOTNOTES: DALLAS ALICE broke well and showed speed between rivals before ceding command, stalked two wide into the turn, remained in the two path to the stretch, took over in upper stretch, cleared at the furlong pole and was kept to task to the wire. ROMAN EMPRESS had to pause behind a rival in traffic early, went two wide into the turn, angled out and came four wide into the lane, put in late run and gained the place. PARCO dueled for the lead outside rivals early then cleared up the backstretch, showed the way along the inside on the turn, lost command in upper stretch and flattened to third. MOONLITE IN HEAVEN vied for command early inside rivals then chased PARCO up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn, tipped two wide into the lane and flattened out. STORM D'ORO bobbled a bit leaving the gate, chased three deep into the turn, spun three wide into the lane, tired in the drive and eased in the final furlong and walked off.

ENTRY.NAME: Dallas Alice
ENTRY.OWNER: Zepeda Racing Inc and Glassman Richard L
ENTRY.COMMENT: ceded, stalked 2wide, cleared 1/8, kept to task

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 89. Starter Allowance Purse 33000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $50,000 OR LESS AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 25 Allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SOUL OF A WARRIOR pressed the pace from outside early, lost touch but remained close on the turn, took aim again four wide into the stretch, gained command past the three-sixteenths pole, cleared in the final furlong and held well. PRECIOUS BABY dropped back early, rounded the bend two then three wide and finished well for second. MODERA had to pause to avoid a shuffle between rivals early, stalked three wide into the turn, exited the bend five wide, kept on in the final furlong and regained the show while making up some ground late. MANGO MOON stepped to the front quickly and set the pace inside SOUL OF A WARRIOR, cleared that rival around the bend, came off the rail and led three wide into the lane and weakened. QUICKLIKEABUNNY tracked along the rail into the turn, spun three wide into the drive and failed to menace.

ENTRY.NAME: Mango Moon
ENTRY.COMMENT: speed, cleared turn, overtaken upper, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Modera
ENTRY.COMMENT: paused early, stalked off rail, 3-5wide, kept on

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 3 5F Dirt CR: 88. Claiming Purse 25000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000.

CLAIM.OWNER: Battle Born Racing Stable Voss Jackie and Glatt Mark

RACE.FOOTNOTES: AMERICAN CAT set the pace under pressure between rivals, cleared while drifting out around the bend, drifted in under right-handed urging at the gap, switch to the left-hand in the final furlong and held well. WORTH LOOKING got bumped leaving the gate, put in tight quarters shortly after, chased between into the turn, went between foes again around the bend, looked to challenge inside the AMERICAN CAT but had that rider drift across his path and had to alter out, then finished willingly to outkick ABERDEEN'S KNIGHT for third. ABERDEEN'S KNIGHT showed brief speed then chased along the inside, put in a mild bid nearing the eighth pole but faltered in deep stretch. MEDINA MAN tracked three deep into the turn, five wide into the stretch and failed to menace. HOT MEMORIES broke out and bumped, went up to press the issue from outside, could not keep up with the winner around the bend, chased three wide and three deep leaving the bend and faded in the lane.PER RULING FROM HIWU, AMERICAN CAT WAS DISQUALIFIED FOR POSITIVE TEST.

ENTRY.NAME: Aberdeen's Knight
ENTRY.COMMENT: brief speed, chased inside, mild bid 1/8, faltered

ENTRY.NAME: dq-American Cat
ENTRY.OWNER: Belico Racing LLC Ruiz Lorenzo and Valdez Jaime
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pressured pace, cleared turn, drifted 4wide, drifted in, best

ENTRY.NAME: Worth Looking
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, lost path early, altered str, willingly

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 4 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 71. Maiden Claiming Purse 20000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CALIFORNIA BLING got bumped by inner rival leaving the gate, chased four wide into the turn, five wide into the lane, rallied to the front midstretch, kicked clear under right-handed urging and won going away. AMAZING FLYER pressed between foes early, dueled outside OAK CREEK GAL around the bend, put a head in front at the quarter pole, could not offer any resistance to the winner in midstretch and stayed on to secure second. TIGER'S WISH hit the gate and bumped outer rival, attended the pace three deep into the turn, could not keep up past the three-eighths pole, chased three wide into the lane and churned on through the final furlong for the show. ROUND IN CIRCLES climbed a bit when hit with the kickback behind rivals, chased two wide into the turn, remained off the rail trailing into the stretch and failed to menace. OAK CREEK GAL set the pace under pressure from inner rivals, dueled with AMAZING FLYER through the turn, lost command at the quarter pole and tired in the final furlong.

ENTRY.NAME: Oak Creek Gal
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pressured pace, dueled inside, tired

ENTRY.NAME: Amazing Flyer
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed between, dueled outside, led 1/4, held 2nd

ENTRY.NAME: Tiger's Wish
ENTRY.OWNER: River Bend Farm (Winick) Tannyhill William Michael and Weeks Gregory L
ENTRY.COMMENT: hit gate/bumped start, attended pace 3deep, churned on

ENTRY.NAME: California Bling
ENTRY.OWNER: Ray Stan and Reeve III Thomas Var

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 5 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 65. Maiden Claiming Purse 20000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PRINCESS MAGIC took control early, led two then three wide around the turn, drifted in at the three-sixteenths pole while opening up and was ridden out in deep stretch. ASSUREDLY chased from outside early, rounded the bend four wide, finished willingly but had to settle for second best. ARTEMIS STAR fractious in the gate, hustled early and pressed the pace between rivals, could not keep up with the leader on the turn, angled over to the inside and flattened in the stretch run. MIDNIGHT SUSI dropped back early, saved ground then angled out into the stretch and was along for the show. MENSA ON TAP raced up close three deep to the turn, chased the winner three wide into the lane and weakened. WARREN'S SHOW BIZZ stumbled badly and lost the rider at the start, was quickly caught by the outrider and walked off.

ENTRY.NAME: Midnight Susi
ENTRY.COMMENT: dropped back, inside, angled out into str, gained 3rd

ENTRY.NAME: Warren's Show Bizz
ENTRY.OWNER: Warren Benjamin C and Warren Sally

ENTRY.NAME: Artemis Star
ENTRY.OWNER: Firsthome Thoroughbreds Sebold Racing LLC Ahern Joseph Kevin and Jeffries Samant
ENTRY.COMMENT: fractious, hustled, pressed between, angled in turn, flattened

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 6 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 89. Claiming Purse 29000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000, if for $22,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Maidens Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BIG SWEDE hit the gate and got bumped in the beginning, chased three wide off the pace into the turn, four wide turning for home, moved out further in the lane, closed steadily through the drive and got up in the closing moments. JAM SESSION chased outside a rival then three wide on the turn, bumped with inner foe at the quarter pole, reached the front midstretch, held a short lead into the final sixteenth and was caught in the final strides. CURLY ESA tracked along the inside into the turn, angled out and came four wide into the lane, bid five deep in the drive, fought outside JAM SESSION in the furlong grounds and could not get by. SPIRITIST got bumped into inner rival at the start, lagged behind wide up the backstretch, navigated the turn four then five wide, closed widest in the lane and gained a minor award. WEGONAHAVAGOODTIME dueled for command from inside, fought to midstretch and flattened. STORMY SAMURAI bumped inner rival at the start, went up to duel from outside, had the rider lose his whip at the quarter pole and weakened. SQUARE CAT chased two wide through the turn, bumped outer rival at the quarter pole and weakened. DUE TO A TIMER MALFUNCTION, THE SIXTH RACE WAS HAND-TIMED.

ENTRY.NAME: Wegonahavagoodtime
ENTRY.OWNER: Belico Racing LLC Medina Lizbeth and Pineda Milton

ENTRY.NAME: Jam Session
ENTRY.OWNER: Eclipse Thoroughbred Partners and Colburn Harold

ENTRY.NAME: Stormy Samurai
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, dueled outside, lost whip 1/4, weakened

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 7 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 91. Maiden Special Weight Purse 45000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Cal-Bred or Cal-Sired horses Allowed a Three (3) Pound Weight Allowance.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WICKLINE went to take control from WILL BE, set the pace with rivals on both sides early, led two wide around the bend and three wide into the lane, cleared WILL BE in upper stretch and inched away under a drive. WILL BE away quickly from inside, pressured WICKLINE from inside, lost touch with that rival in upper stretch but remained close into the final furlong, faltered a bit late but proved second best. CENTRAL DISPATCH pressed three deep up the backstretch, lost touch with WICKLINE around the bend, chased four wide into the drive, drifted out and in through the lane and kept on for a clear third. STAVROS stalked the leaders from outside, driven four to five wide into the stretch and weakened. CONFUCIUS lacked early speed, went two then three wide around the bend, shifted in upper stretch and failed to menace. BENELLI traveled towards the rear in the early going, saved ground around the bend and failed to make an impact. LEVON broke a bit slow, chased off the pace two wide through the turn and was never a factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 8 1M Dirt CR: 102. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 47000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING OR STARTER OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $40,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Other Than Maiden, Claim ing Or Starter Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $40,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: REDLINE got shuffled between rivals prior to the first turn then tracked three deep, remained outside rivals into the far turn, loomed five wide into the lane, challenged FINNEUS from outside, dueled through the final furlong and drew clear in the end. FINNEUS was a bit rank chasing three wide to the outside of the leader around the first turn, remained closest in the middle stages, challenged around the far turn, drifted out leaving the bend while taking over, put away SHORTMAN at the top of the lane but was soon engaged by REDLINE, dueled with that rival into the final furlong and got outkicked in deep stretch. SHORTMAN chased outside a rival then between leaving the backstretch, took aim three wide into the lane, moved out in upper stretch, tried to rallied between foes midstretch but saw that opening dissolve approaching the eighth pole, gained a clear path once again and kept on for the show. TIDAL FORCES broke out and bumped rival, stalked from inside then a bit off the rail into the backstretch, took aim two wide entering the lane, stayed within striking distance into the final furlong then flattened out. HEMBREE got bumped leaving the gate, settled inside, trailed on the far turn then swung out leaving the bend and could not rally. MUHAMMAD ALI (PER) cleared in the two path into the first turn, showed the way to the far turn, led along the rail while challenged from outside around the bend, relinquished the lead into the lane and gave way.

ENTRY.NAME: Tidal Forces
ENTRY.OWNER: Agave Racing Stable and Sam-Son Farm
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke out, bumped, stalked inside-2wide, flattened
